  "time_ut": 1661940991,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dda \u0d86\u0dba\u0dad\u0db1 \u0d95\u0db1\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0da9\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0da8\u0dbd\u0dd3 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Patali says that there are too many institutions in the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Samagi Jana Balavegaya Party's Colombo District Councilor Mr. Patali Champika Ranawaka said in Parliament today (31) that having only one institution for one work in the country is quite enough.",
        "He also mentioned that there are three institutions in the country only for the development of the coconut industry.",
        "Mr. Ranawaka said this during the debate on the second reading of the Budget Appropriation Bill.",
        "The MP said that he does not believe that profit can be made by privatizing everything and stated that government institutions in this country should be managed.",
        "\"The number of institutions should be reduced to one institution for each work. There are three institutions for coconut development. There are many such institutions in the country. If a formal management audit is done, these institutions can be reduced to one.",
        "\"Negotiations are going on with the financial fund. It may take a year or two to enter into it. During that time, we need to find an alternative way for economic management that is not the financial fund.\""
      ],
